25|$|Another highly {{valuable}} {{variety is}} chrome tourmaline, a rare type of dravite tourmaline from Tanzania. Chrome tourmaline {{is a rich}} green color due {{to the presence of}} chromium atoms in the crystal; chromium also produces the green color of emeralds. Of the standard elbaite colors, blue indicolite gems are typically the most valuable, followed by green verdelite and pink to red rubellite. There are also yellow tourmalines, sometimes known as canary tourmaline. Zambia is rich in both red and yellow tourmaline, which are relatively inexpensive in that country. Ironically the rarest variety, colorless <b>achroite,</b> is not appreciated and is the least expensive of the transparent tourmalines.|$|E
